# Build output
bin/
obj/
*.user

# The global excludes file ignores *.dll. This one is a build INPUT, not output: tlbimp'd once from
# the type library embedded in ONENOTE.EXE, and referenced with EmbedInteropTypes. Without it a
# fresh clone cannot build. See OneNote2Yamlover.OneNote.csproj for how to regenerate it.
!lib/Interop.OneNote.dll

# Converted OneNote content. This is personal data (page text, images, voice recordings) and it is
# regenerated by every sync — it must never enter git history.
sync-output/

# Cached GetHierarchy dump: ~4 MB, contains every notebook/section/page title. Regenerated on demand.
.cache/

# IDE
.idea/
.vs/
